headline: Natural Gas Prices Are a Rollercoaster. The Latest Direction Is Down.
summary: Natural gas prices have been on a wild ride lately, rising and falling based largely on weather forecasts.  Natural gas prices rose to $5.29 on Friday, the highest level since late 2022.  Natural gas is used for both heating and electricity-generation.
